content: Back at this after a couple of years and the disappointment that was Draw Rider 2. It's a great game in the spirit of action supercross / elastomania. Enjoying the new "Challenge" feature with custom courses...except when a buggy or unplayable course pops up in the middle of a challenge, rendering the entire challenge impossible to complete. I mean, come on, dude. Vet the "Challenge" courses a little better. Difficult levels? Definitely. Unplayable poop level made by a 12 year old that smashes you into a wall of bombs in 0.3 seconds? Absolutely not.

content: This is the epitome of a trial and error game, and as such should be avoided by certain types of gamers that get angry at repetition without any real feeling of "I'm improving". Everything is locked behind completing the previous thing, so you will hit a wall before too long, and be unable to progress. It's not really a "git gud" kind of game, but rather a "my brain itches and I feel like throwing my phone into a wall" kind of game.

2 words: 2D TrackMania. I enjoy hunting WRs on Challenge mode, just wish this game had a jFreu feature of some sort that displayed a dismissable leaderboard of the level to the side so you know what time to beat right off the bat instead of guessing. Scriptable object behaviour would be a nice feature too. To anyone wishing to get this game: get it now. If you can't, save up money. If you can't, rob a bank. If you can't, go mine Bitcoin or something.
